{title: Apologize}
{artist: Bill Anderson}
{composer: Written by Michael Gordon and James Griffin}

[C]In the fury of the moment when the words of wrath rang out
When my mind was filled with questions and my [F]head was filled with doubt
I [Fm]can still see all the sadness and the [C]sorrow in your eyes
How can [A#7]flowers live in darkness how can [G7]I apologize
[C]For the blackness I've created in the world that used to shine
I've wilted all the roses and I've [F]spoiled all the wine
Get [Fm]out your magic pencil and [C]erase the cloudy skies
[A#7]Draw a picture of me saying [G7]I apologize
[C]Give me back the [F]words I spoke in [G7]haste
Give 'em [C]back or [F]love will go to [G7]waste
Give 'em [C]b-[G7]a-c[C]-k
See the sunlight reappearing through the shrouds of darkened gloom
As I hear your words forgiving me and [F]watch the flowers bloom
Have [Fm]your arms refused to open have you [C]served all your ties
I'd [A#7]still be on my knees saying [G7]I apologize
[C]Give me back the [F]words I spoke in [G7]haste
